<subSubSection id="C357B3CFFFADFFD4A6ABFB9154F54057" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF2E044FFADFFD4A6ABFB9157454103" blockId="50.[151,634,1077,1099]" box="[151,634,1077,1099]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Species included: 2 (Afrotropical / Palaearctic).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF2E044FFADFFD4A6ABFBD354F54057" blockId="50.[151,1436,1143,1311]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Synapomorphy: Distiphallus with long, obliquely angled, posteriorly-directed spine basally (44). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC9DB5FFADFFD4A2C1FBDC50A341C7" author="Tsacas, L." box="[1277,1436,1143,1167]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="145 - 171" refId="ref108265" refString="Tsacas, L. (1977) Les Curtonotidae (Diptera) de l'Afrique: 1. Le genre Curtonotum Macquart. Annals of the Natal Museum, 23, 145 - 171." type="journal article" year="1977">Tsacas (1977)</bibRefCitation>
included the two sister species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D9BC7FFADFFD4A435FB3857C941FB" authority="Tsacas" authorityName=": Wirth and Tsacas" authorityYear="1980" box="[521,758,1180,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saheliense">
<emphasis id="B9393C56FFADFFD4A435FB38572341FC" box="[521,540,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9393C56FFADFFD4A411FB38579D41FC" box="[557,674,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">saheliense</emphasis>
Tsacas
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D9BC7FFADFFD4A50FFB3856CE41FB" authority="Tsacas" authorityName=": Wirth and Tsacas" authorityYear="1980" box="[819,1009,1180,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simile">
<emphasis id="B9393C56FFADFFD4A50FFB38567941FC" box="[819,838,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9393C56FFADFFD4A56BFB3856A541FC" box="[855,922,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">simile</emphasis>
Tsacas
</taxonomicName>
, both of which are confined to xeric habitats bordering the Sahara and the Arabian Peninsula, in his 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D9BC7FFADFFD4A5B8FB64512F4190" authorityName="Duda (PPRI" authorityYear="1935" box="[900,1040,1216,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuthbertsoni">
<emphasis id="B9393C56FFADFFD4A5B8FB64512F4190" box="[900,1040,1216,1240]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">cuthbertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. As attested by the above-mentioned synapomorphy, they are here regarded as being sufficiently distinct to warrant inclusion in a species-group of their own.
</paragraph>
